data.content:
Build succeeds and all 3 tests pass. Here's what changed:

```csharp
// Before (MSTest v2)                        // After (MSTest v3)
Assert.AreEqual(expected, actual);        →  Assert.AreEqual<object>(expected, actual);
Assert.AreNotEqual(a, b);                →  Assert.AreNotEqual<object>(a, b);
Assert.AreSame(obj, obj);                →  Assert.AreSame<object>(obj, obj);
```

**Why:** MSTest v3 removed the `Assert.AreEqual(object, object)` overload. The fix is adding an explicit generic type parameter — `<object>` works when your variables are typed as `object`. If you know the concrete type, prefer that (e.g., `Assert.AreEqual<int>(...)`) for stronger type checking.
